The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, May 27: Thousands of military veterans today went on a symbolic hunger strike demanding better retirement benefits and a revision of salaries for serving soldiers.           
	The show has embarrassed the government, prompting the minister of state for defence, Pallam Raju, to say it is unbecoming on the part of the dignified ex-servicemen to launch hunger strike. It provoked the veterans, whose spokesperson Major General (retired) Satbir Singh said: It is a sad day when a minister of state for defence has to make such a loose statement....                  
	Chennai: Some 240-odd passengers heaved a sigh of relief on Tuesday as their British Airways flight touched down safe after fears of a full emergency landing. A hydraulic problem caused a technical snag. Luckily, there was no belly landing, a source said.                  
	Jammu (PTI): The Jammu and Kashmir government on Tuesday banned the movement of more than four persons near the International Border and the sale of combat outfit in Samba district for two months. The steps follow reports of infiltration across the border and use of Indian combat outfits by the infiltrators in Samba.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Karnataka governor Rameshwar Thakur on Tuesday invited the BJPs chief ministerial candidate, B.S. Yediyurappa, to form the government. Earlier, the Centre revoked the Presidents rule in the state following the completion of the election process.                  
	Islamabad (PTI): An Indian teenager wowed Pakistanis at a classical concert by children in Islamabad. Thirteen-year-old Aditee Bhalla, daughter of the Indian naval attach in Pakistan, sang Joseph Hadyns Piercing Eyes and played Two German Dances at the Austrian high commissioners home this weekend.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): Madras High Court has declined to stay the trial court proceedings against ADMK general secretary Jayalalithaa in a wealth tax case.                                                                                                                         
